5|$|In 1478, the Catholic Monarchs of Spain, Ferdinand II of Aragon and Isabella I of Castile, {{established}} an ecclesiastical tribunal {{known as the}} Spanish Inquisition. It was intended to maintain Catholic orthodoxy in their kingdoms. Hundreds of <b>Jews</b> <b>were</b> killed, and their synagogues destroyed. One {{of the consequences of}} these disturbances was the mass forced conversion of Jews.|$|E
